What are the different control flow statements available in Java?
Control flow stratements are categorized into 3 types : Selection, Iteration and jump statements.
Selection statements(Decision making statements) ; if else switch [True or Flase]
Iteration statements : A block a code is repeatedly executed for specific number of times- for, while, do while, for each.
Jump statements : Alters or transfers the contol to other section of the program- break, continue


What is the difference between break and continue statements?
The break keyword is used to stop a loop execution, which may be a for, while, do while or for each.
The continue keyword is used to skip the particular recursion only in a loop execution, which may be a for, while, do while or for each.
